<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>What typically happens to velocity (V) in the equation of exchange (MV = PY) during a recession?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Velocity increases as people spend more quickly</option>
            <option letter="b">Velocity decreases as people hold onto money longer</option>
            <option letter="c">Velocity remains exactly constant</option>
            <option letter="d">Velocity increases proportionally with money supply</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>During recessions, velocity typically decreases because people and businesses become more cautious with spending and prefer to hold onto money longer. This precautionary behavior means each dollar circulates more slowly through the economy, reducing the velocity of money.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
